. If you have two tables Customers and Orders and you want to update the OrderStatus column in the Orders table to
Shipped for all orders placed by customers where the City, within the Customers table, is New York, which T-SQL 
Statement would you execute? 1
• UPDATE Orders SET OrderStatus = 'Shipped' WHERE City = 'New York';
• UPDATE Customers SET OrderStatus = 'Shipped' WHERE City = 'New York';
• UPDATE o SET OrderStatus = 'Shipped' FROM Orders o INNER JOIN Customers c ON o.CustomerID = c.CustomerID
WHERE c.City = 'New York';
